    "comment": "Rationale: Co-localizes with acetylcholine receptors (AChRs) in mouse NMJ, fluorescence imaging + fig4. Rabsyn is surface expressed, can be deleted/rescued by mutation of AChR interacting domain in myoblasts.\n\n\"Altogether, these results strongly suggest that AChRs serve as a mediator for the targeting and association of rapsyn with the postsynaptic membrane at synaptic sites.\". Experimental description: PMID:11087759 from Jonathan Cohen's group appears to be the source for the Rapsyn-EGFP constructs. This paper mentions the construct is based on mouse species.\n\nthe cultures were also based on mouse species;\n\"MICE, MUSCLE DENERVATION, PLASMID ELECTROPORATION, ACHR LABELING, AND NMJ IMAGING. In this study, female non-Swiss albino mice (6-10 weeks old, 20-30 g) were used.\"",
